{"word":"νότιος","slug":"νότιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νότιος</b></el> <el>(νότιος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νότος'><el>νότος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>wet, moist, damp</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:— <el>ἐν νοτίῳ</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>the open sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>southern</i>, <el>ν. θάλασσα</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> the Indian ocean, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}